Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a @salt{pinch} on to boil for the pasta. Pop the @British beef mince{240%g} in a #mixing bowl{} with @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @tomato ketchup{1/2%tbsp}, a @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} and half the @hard Italian style cheese{10%g}(grated). Mix together with your hands and shape into four meatballs per person.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Heat a glug of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the meatballs and cook until browned on the outside, ~{10-11%minutes}. Gently turn occasionally. Once brown pour in the @chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%jar} together with the @water{30%ml}, @Worcester sauce{7.5%ml}, a @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some), @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}. Carefully stir together, bring to the boil and then lower the heat to medium. Simmer, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Add the @fusilli{160%g} to your pan of boiling water and simmer until cooked, ~{9-10%minutes}. Add the @baby spinach{62.5%g} to the pasta water and submerge for the last ~{2%minutes}.

Finely chop the @parsley{}(stalks and all). Chop the @medium tomato{1} into 1⁄2cm cubes. Pop the parsley and tomato into a #small bowl{} with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}. Stir together.

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Drain the pasta and spinach then return to the saucepan. Pour over the meatballs and sauce and stir gently to combine. Tip the whole mixture into a large, deep #ovenproof dish{}. Drain the @mozzarella{1/2%ball} and tear it over the meatballs and pasta. Sprinkle over the remaining @hard Italian style cheese{10%g}(grated), season with a grind of @black pepper{} and grill until the cheese is golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch it doesn't burn!

Spoon the cheesy meatball bake into bowls and serve with the tomato salsa on top for the adults. Enjoy!